        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2007-04-02T14:30:21.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>I'm not sure it makes sense to do so, considering the current architecture of the REST client. Currently, it simply makes HTTP GET and POST requsts -- no XML is actually transmitted in the request. In other words, the content length of a given request will be governed by, at most, the values being passed in a POST request. Additionally, this is automagically taken care of by Zend_Http_Client when the request is actually made.</p>

<p>For this request to have more value, the REST client would need to be able to send over XML as raw POST data -- something not currently supported.</p>

        </div>
